text: Karan-Kunkas () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Karanovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 407 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 41 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Karan-Kunkas
